This paper deals with community detection in networks, which is a topic that can fall under several sub-categories in computer science. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), as the paper specifically focuses on weighted networks and their community structure. Another likely category is cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper proposes a new community extraction algorithm and benchmarks it against existing methods. The paper also uses statistical methods and null models, which could place it in the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with simulations and real-world networks, which could place it in the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
